@startuml IRouter_removeLiquidityRecovery
actor User
participant Router
participant Vault
participant Hooks

== Initiation ==
User -> Router: removeLiquidityRecovery(pool, exactBptAmountIn, minAmountsOut)
note right: User initiates liquidity removal in Recovery Mode.

== Vault Unlocking ==
Router -> Vault: unlock(encoded params)
note right: Router encodes parameters and unlocks Vault for processing.

== Remove Liquidity Recovery Hook ==
Vault -> Router: removeLiquidityRecoveryHook(pool, sender, exactBptAmountIn, minAmountsOut)
note right: Vault triggers Router's recovery hook.

== Recovery Logic ==
Router -> Vault: removeLiquidityRecovery(pool, sender, exactBptAmountIn, minAmountsOut)
note right: Router requests Vault to execute recovery removal.

alt shouldCallBeforeRemoveLiquidity == true
    Vault -> Hooks: onBeforeRemoveLiquidity(...)
    note right: Optional pre-removal hook if configured.
    Hooks --> Vault: true
end alt

Vault -> Vault: computeProportionalAmountsOut(balancesRaw, totalSupply, exactBptAmountIn)
note right: Vault calculates proportional token amounts from raw balances.

alt shouldCallAfterRemoveLiquidity == true
    Vault -> Hooks: onAfterRemoveLiquidity(...)
    note right: Optional post-removal hook if configured.
    Hooks --> Vault: true
end alt

Vault --> Router: amountsOut

== Token Transfers ==
loop for each token in tokens
    Router -> Vault: sendTo(token, user, amountsOut[i])
    note right: Router directs Vault to transfer tokens to user.
    Vault -> User: transfer token
    note right: Vault sends tokens to user.
end loop

== Finalization ==
Router -> User: amountsOut
note right: Router returns withdrawn token amounts to user.

@enduml